{ The Caro-Kann Defense begins after white plays 1.e4. We are going to play c6. }
1. e4 c6 { Here, white can still play a number of moves, but the most common is taking the full center. After this, we are going to play d5. } 2. d4 d5 { From here, white has four typical moves: The Exchange Variation (Blue), The Advance Variation (Yellow), or defending the pawn with either the knight (Green) or a pawn (Red). } { [%csl Gc3,Bd5,Rf3,Ye5][%cal Gb1c3,Be4d5,Rf2f3,Ye4e5] } *


[Event "The Caro-Kann: The Advance Variation - White Captures"]
[Date "2026.05.24"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "B12"]
[Opening "Caro-Kann Defense: Advance Variation, Botvinnik-Carls Defense"]
[StudyName "The Caro-Kann"]
[ChapterName "The Advance Variation - White Captures"]
