[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Booros"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pp2pppp/2p5/3p4/3PP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2026.05.24"]
[UTCTime "21:44:12"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

3. e5 { First we are going to look at the advance variation. Here we are going to push our c pawn. } 3... c5 4. dxc5 { If white captures here, we are going to move our knight out to c3. } 4... Nc6 5. Nf3 { Once we see the knight come out, we are going to pin it. } 5... Bg4 6. Be2 { Wait! Don't go for the knight and pawn yet! We aren't going to take that pawn until we are pressured to do so. It isn't going anywhere, and we don't want to weaken our queenside without reason. Instead, close the center up and defend your d pawn with a pawn. } 6... e6 7. Be3 { We are looking to take back the c pawn, but if it gets defended, we are going to look to get our other knight out. Do you see how? } 7... Nge7 8. O-O { Finish getting the knight out. } 8... Nf5 { Our knight likes to live on this square if we can get the bishop out to g4. Whenever our bishop gets attacked, we are going to take and then take the pawn on e5. } *


