3. f3 { A tricky line to play against the Fantasy could be e5, the idea being to get your queen and dark squared bishop out quickly to target down the a7-g1 diagonal } { [%csl Ge5,Gc5,Gb6][%cal Ge7e5,Gd8b6,Gf8c5] } 3... e5 4. dxe5 { Get the bishop out. } 4... Bc5 5. exd5 { Get the queen out. } 5... Qb6 6. Ne2 { This is a horrible move for white. We are only looking at it to show the potency of this variation. Find mate in 2. } 6... Bf2+ 7. Kd2 { Nice catch! Finish the job! } 7... Qe3# *


