2. Nf3 { If we see the knight come out, we can still play our pawn up in the same fashion. This will either be something along the lines of the Dinic gambit, or the Two Knights. } 2... d5 3. Nc3 { If we see the Two Knights, we have two options. The first is to take the pawn, and bring our knight out, playing it like the Classical Variation. The second, and what we do in this study, is to pin the knight to the queen, and then bring our pawn up to support our d-pawn. } 3... Bg4 4. h3 { If they attack our bishop, we are going to take the knight. } 4... Bxf3 5. Qxf3 { Support your pawn. } 5... e6 6. Be2 { We can play this like the Fantasy here, with a kingside fianchetto, if we wish. } 6... g6 7. d3 { Finish the fianchetto. } 7... Bg7 *


